Remember that beautiful things can bloom from the seeds of your most difficult times. 

My fiancé woke me up to breakfast, a matcha and handwritten note. Then took me out to take some photos. It’s the small acts of service that remind me why God chose him as a life partner for me. 

Mental health is so wild to me cause life can be so perfect around you, job going well, fab friends and you still get this little thought of damn life sucks. Imposture syndrome in every aspect. An overwhelming emotion of doubt. It’s important in those moments to do things that fill your cup. And to trust in whatever higher power you want that it’ll pass. I love you.

Fall is here!?!? 

I live in Southern California, so truthfully it never actually feels like fall sadly. But I can feel a little bit into the spooky season better with seasonal drinks ;) 

Pumpkin spiced matcha is my new go to. The matcha gives me energy to tackle to day and the pumpkin makes my heart warm. It’s also super easy to make. I learned this cold foam and I’m annoying obsessed. 

Ingredients: 
@chamberlaincoffee matcha powder. 
Any milk of your choice

For the cold foam: 
Heavy whipping cream 
Pumpkin purée 
Maple syrup
Pumpkin spice 

Make the match is HOT water then pour your cooler milk overtop. Place cold foam on everything and mix mix mix. Or just leave sd a floated, it’s YOUR DRINK do what YOU want. Ya feel me?

Journaling in a devotion offers a sacred space to pour our hearts and thoughts.

Through gratitude, prayers, and reflections, we uncover the divine within.

I truly think we don’t celebrate our friends enough. 

At this age everything is changing. We become busy with work, family, significant others. My friends a year ago wanted to change that, always making sure to “celebrate the small wins” 

As you grow older you look for very different things in people.
Honesty. Loyalty. Integrity. But most of all, you look for someone who will stand right by your side when the walls start crumbling and the fires rage within. And I’m incredibly blessed to have found those friends 

I believe friends should be made to feel special everyday, celebrated everyday. Making these advent calendars and watching their faces light up like children running down to see Santa’s gifts Christmas Day warmed me up inside.  I recommend this gift idea to anyone who wants to be extra and make someone’s holiday feel as special as them ❤️
